==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ingurgitation
<hw>In*gur`gi*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ingurgitatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>ingurgitation</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The act of swallowing greedily or immoderately; that which is so
swallowed.</def> <rj><au>E. Darwin.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He drowned his stomach and senses with a large draught and
<qex>ingurgitation</qex> of wine.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ingustable</ent>⟦br⟧
